@node "HTML" "HyperText Markup Language"

   HTML (or HyperText Markup Language) is the language of the World Wide Web. HTML is based on
SGML (Standardized General Markup Language). HTML allows you to compose ASCII hypertext
documents that can, in either text or graphical form, combine text, pictures, sounds,
animation, links to other documents on your machine, links to pages on other machines, and
links to other Internet services (such as telnet, gopher, ftp, usenet news, etc.). A much
better description of HTML, as well as a comprehensive guide to all current HTML 3.0 codes,
can be found in the file @{"HTML_Guide.guide" link "HTML_Guide" 0}, available on Aminet and also included in this
archive.
@endnode

